{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticMutexProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP","text":"PointerWrapper"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prior to GLib 2.32, GStaticMutex had the significant advantage"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that it doesn’t need to be created at run-time, but can be defined"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at compile-time. Since 2.32, "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"type":"text","text":" can be statically allocated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as well, and GStaticMutex has been deprecated."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a version of our "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"give_me_next_number()"},{"type":"text","text":" example using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a GStaticMutex:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static int current_number = 0;","    int ret_val;","    static GStaticMutex mutex = G_STATIC_MUTEX_INIT;","","    g_static_mutex_lock (&mutex);","    ret_val = current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","    g_static_mutex_unlock (&mutex);","","    return ret_val;","  }"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Sometimes you would like to dynamically create a mutex. If you don’t"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"want to require prior calling to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"type":"text","text":", because your code"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"should also be usable in non-threaded programs, you are not able to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_mutex_new()"},{"type":"text","text":" and thus "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"type":"text","text":", as that requires a prior call to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"type":"text","text":". In these cases you can also use a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It must be initialized with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" before using it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and freed with with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_free()"},{"type":"text","text":" when not needed anymore to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"free up any allocated resources."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even though "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":" is not opaque, it should only be used with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the following functions, as it is defined differently on different"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"platforms."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions apart from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_get_mutex()"},{"type":"text","text":" can also be used even if "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"has not yet been called. Then they do nothing, apart from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_trylock()"},{"type":"text","text":" which does nothing but returning "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions are actually macros. Apart from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"taking their addresses, you can however use them as if they were"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functions."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef"},{"type":"text","text":" as a lighweight, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/staticmutexprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","doc:\/\/GLib\/documenta